  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/46a9796f20f247dbb1f8d9004485fc5a",
      "title": "Monsters as adventurers?",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Imagine a goblin scurrying around in the corner of a cave, cutting off the ears of enemies, a kobold disarming traps, so that his companions - a huge orc, a flexible snake woman and a hobgoblin samurai - made their way further down the corridor and caught the wyvern by surprise... In fact, together with Volo's Guide to Monsters, we have</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">there is an opportunity to create adventurer monsters!</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Let's imagine several options for who the monster-heroes might be and why they set off in search of adventure.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/39e397fa61084c8e8d305b0e19bbb3ca",
      "title": "Goblin-Ranger",
      "content": "<p>Goblins are nimble little creatures that can use a bonus action to hide and move away from enemies, as well as deal bonus damage to all creatures that are larger than them.</p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Goblins are primitive creatures who love to collect shiny trinkets and tame giant rats.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">They live in tribes that obey a shaman and are deathly afraid of the dark gods they worship.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Therefore, the adventurer will most likely be an exiled goblin.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The shaman sent your squad on a mission at the call of the deity, and in the bloody carnage, only you survived. After returning to the tribe, you learned that no god-willed task existed, and the shaman simply laid his paws on your squad's property. You're looking for ways to get revenge on the outside world, so you work as a guide through the wild lands for other adventurers.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/0355c01e477d4ecdad617607316d45c2",
      "title": "Hobgoblin-Warrior",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Hobgoblins are true apprentices of war, who perfectly master weapons and armor.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">In the presence of allies, the hobgoblin does not want to hit its face in the dirt, so it receives bonuses to saves and checks.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Hobgoblins are the pinnacle of goblinoid evolution. They create military empires that march victoriously through the lands of other races, subjugating entire countries. War is the meaning of life for every hobgoblin, so an adventurer can become both a loner expelled from the empire and a young warrior looking for military glory in foreign lands.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">You showed yourself brilliantly on the battlefield. Your parents and gods were proud of you until you had several fingers chopped off in another battle. You wanted to show that this injury wouldn't affect your skills, but it showed. Soon, everyone turned away from you, like a cripple. In search of work, you joined a caravan and traveled far from your home empire, no longer as a valiant warrior, but as a mercenary, hoping to heal your arm and return home.</span><span class=\"ryNqvb\"></span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/0130af5f60f94a4eb048767e880438fe",
      "title": "Kobold-Wizard",
      "content": "<p>Kobolds are small dragon-like creatures that work well in a team and can distract opponents by begging for mercy.</p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Kobolds are a race of dragon servants who usually live near the dragon's lair and help it in every way.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Like the dragons themselves, they are greedy for treasure, but unlike their masters, they are extremely weak and cowardly, so they prefer to attack the enemy with a hawk.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">You were born into the service of a red dragon, and from childhood you were different from your siblings. An unquenchable flame burned in your chest, and sparks flew from your nostrils. When your parents saw you lighting a fire, they forbade you to use this power. When you grew up, your relatives told you with tears in their eyes that the lord kills all the kobolds with such power. You left the dragon cave with a firm determination to tame the power of the inner flame and free the tribe from the tyrants.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/aee4836264ff4b47b17c9fd74fb9da15",
      "title": "Yuan-Ti Rogue",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Yuan-ti are half-human, half-snake, flexible and agile.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">They have an innate resistance to magic, know how to spit poison and talk to snakes.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The Yuan-ti are a terrible race born from the forbidden rituals of the fusion of humans and snakes. The pure-blooded rulers of this forgotten empire consider it perfection to transform into an intelligent snake.<span class=\"jCAhz\"> </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\"><span class=\"jCAhz\">After the ritual, you were not too perfect - you are distinguished from a human only by the scales on your face and snake eyes. All the better for your purpose. The rulers created a fake identity for you and sent you to the human kingdoms as a spy. Now you wear a mask and seek out adventures for a fee, scrutinizing local customs and finding vulnerabilities in city defenses. True, sometimes it seems to you that other races are not so bad as they were told in the homeland.</span></span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/f7e8f1dd87be4bad98e141c5a2324db6",
      "title": "Orc-Barbarian",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Orcs are enormous in size and strength, capable of moving swiftly across the battlefield, and excel at surviving in the wilderness.</span><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\"> </span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Orcs are a nomadic people who value strength above all else.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Their gods throw the tribes into battle every time, causing civilized lands to shudder as another horde invades their territory.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Orcs are not very successful in blacksmithing, and their ferocious nature makes it difficult for them to coordinate among themselves.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">In another campaign, the gods turned their backs on you, and several enemy soldiers drove their blades into your back. The last thing you saw was a battlefield, covered in blood and a woman in rags. You came to your senses inside a huge ancient oak tree. In your rage, you tried to continue the fight and kill your savior, but you were so weakened that you couldn't even move. This human woman fed and cared for you. While you were inside the tree, animals and birds talked to you. When you fully regained consciousness surrounded by the forest dwellers, the woman disappeared. All she left behind was an amulet with the image of a mighty tree. You vowed to find a savior.</span></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"jCAhz\"><span class=\"ryNqvb\">These are just a few examples of backstories for monster characters. Don't be afraid to try new things, fantasize and play Dungeons and Dragons!</span></span></p>"
    }
  ],
